Upper Outer Glute Exercises Choosing 2 of you to dive into any single program in my app! Tag a friend & let me know which one you’re ready for! 🤩 I don’t know about you but gimme alll the exercises to make my glutes more round & perky, right?! I’m coming off the hardest longest bulk I have ever done with the intent to gain more muscle in my lower body, esp glutes. I spent the last 6 months working towards this goal but with that came some extra fat (globally). I naturally have a more square figure so my training regime has a strong emphasis on creating more of an hourglass appearance. Give these killer exercises a try and let me know how it goes! 👇🏼 1. Smith Side Lying Abductions I tapped into my glutes so hard with this exercise that I was sore for days! If the bar irritates you, throw a bar pad on. Your top AND bottom knees will be abducting. I use the cue of an accordion 🪗 opening & closing and I’m sticking with it because it’s perfect! 2. Bench Double Quadruped Transverse Abductions This is a new fav! I played around with this and felt the muscles firing the most using the bench. Notice how my hip dips down and I slightly rotate my chest towards the bench for the most stretch and lengthening possible. 3. Hip Shifts + Abduction This exercise will let you know real quick if either hip lacks ER or IR or both. My left hip is moving through ER as I sink into my right hip that’s being pulled into IR. You will feel a nice deep stretch in your right glute before reversing the movement and abducting with your left leg. Join me in my app on my website! 📱 Our Core Challenge starts next week!! You sent an attachment.
When you do a bench press lying flat on your back (flat barbell bench press), you're working your chest muscles but not as much as when you do the bench press on an angle (incline bench press). Imagine trying to push a heavy box on the floor versus trying to push it uphill. Pushing it uphill is harder, right? That's kind of like the difference between a flat and incline bench press. On an incline, you're working your chest muscles a bit harder, especially the upper part. Plus, you're also working your shoulder muscles more. Also, using a barbell for a bench press can be a bit tougher on your shoulders compared to using dumbbells. This is because with a barbell, your hands and arms are stuck in one position. But with dumbbells, your arms can move more naturally, which is easier on your shoulders. This is kind of like how it's easier to carry a backpack when the straps are adjusted just right, rather than too tight or too loose. So, overall, incline bench press with dumbbells can be a bit better for building up your chest muscles and keeping your shoulders safe compared to flat barbell bench press.

It takes a very strong, brave and courageous person to do this. That being said, I believe it to be very interesting situation to be in. To have competed against a person who visually appears to be a man in a powerlifting competition. Being that I am always open and true with you all. I like to talk about topic that may be difficult to talk about, but deserve our attention. I feel that this is a great opportunity to open a space for discussion. In a way this is respectful and productive. The talk is usually about biological men competing in women’s sports. But it is rare to hear of a woman competing against another biological woman who has hormonally transitioned into the appearance of a man. We can all undeniably agree on that a hormonal transition to that extent contributes to an immense strength gain. Now, what are your thoughts on this? Do you believe it to be fair? Where do you see sports categories going in the future? Or do you believe that persons who have transitioned should compete in their own category? Again, I want this to be a respectful and courteous discussion. I will not tolerate any bashing, discourtesy, or hateful comments towards this competitor or the community. If anyone engages in any of the above, their comment will be deleted and the person will be blocked. I also want to thank @alextilinca a friend from the bodybuilding community who I highly respect. Try this⚡️ …The Rolling leg curl is a good, closed chain, hip dominant exercise that simultaneously works the muscles involved in knee flexion and hip extension, increases strength and improves coordination among the muscles of the posterior chain (muscles that connect your glutes and hamstrings that people often refer to as the glute-ham tie-in). You can add some resistance (treadmill) and make it more challenging and fun. You can hold for a bit when the legs are extended to make it more challenging. Do not try this if: * You are a beginner (or the exercise is new to you…try it after you have mastered it on the ground) * Are recovering from injury or surgery involving the back, spine or neck * Have injuries or instability in the knee * Have recently had a knee or hip surgery * Have ruptured or torn ligaments in the knee or ankle #reels #explorepage #viralvideos #trending #tutorial #workout #glutehamworkout #fit #fitness #fitnessmotivation #traceyfarah #stayfit #sports #youcandoit #save #share #tryit #challengeyourself #creative

Two brothers in Turkey's Kahramanmaras city survived for more than 200 hours under the rubble of the Turkey-Syria #earthquake by eating protein powder and drinking their own urine. The New York Times reported that Abdulbaki Yeninar, 21, and his brother Muhammed Enes Yeninar, 17, were pulled out from under the twisted metal and concrete of their collapsed apartment block on Tuesday. The brothers rationed body-building supplements between themselves and drank their own urine to survive, The Times reported. A local news publication, Ihlas News Agency, filmed the two being wheeled into a hospital on stretchers, with oxygen masks on. The media outlet reported that the boys were in good condition. 🚨 Graston application: The aim of the technique is to provide soft tissue mobilization by opening scar (adherent) tissues and increasing circulation. Graston massage is especially preferred to increase the mobility of the fascia and to treat tears or injuries in muscle, tendon and soft tissue.   Medical therapy aims to relax the muscles with myofacial therapy methods by detecting the muscle groups that are tense, painful and causing restriction of movement.   Deep tissue massage is effective in injuries to deep structures such as muscles, tendons, or ligaments. This effect is very strong. Sometimes many structures where exercise and manipulation are not effective can be mobilized through deep friction massage. 🚨Graston uygulaması Kas gruplarının belirginleşmesinde ya da şeklinde değişiklik yaratır mı ? Graston uygulaması Tekniğin amacı skar (yapışık) dokuları açarak ve dolaşımı artırarak yumuşak doku mobilizasyonunu sağlamaktır. Graston masajı, özellikle fasyanın mobilitesini (hareketliliği) arttırmak için kullanılır peki düşük ya oranında Kas gruplarının belirginleşmesinde ya da şeklinde değişiklik yaratır mı Yukarda okumuş olduğunuz bilgi grastonun genel özelliği peki bu bilgilere dayanarak Kasın etrafını bir jelatin gibi saran fascial doku yapılan işlemler ile daha iyi beslenir ve yaşanan fascial yapışıklıklar Çözülür diyebiliriz ve bunlar sayasinde fascial dokunun esnekliği artar. Kasın Bilinçli bir Şekilde kasılmasıyla enine olan büyümesi artacaktır Ancak yapılan işlem kası büyütmez Sadece var olan potansiyeli daha iyi ortaya çıkartır 👊🏼☺️

Hopefully it’s obvious that this clip isn’t meant to be specifically about @wiilliamli, as I’m personally not in the business of doing “natty or nots”. I’m just using this clip to discuss the larger point, which is that because of various factors like leanness, genetics, angles, lighting, pumps etc. it can often be hard to judge someone’s true size through the screen alone. A lean 160 pound dude with favorable shape/insertions and who knows how to display their physique on camera in the most favorable way can very often look bigger in photos and videos than someone 30-40+ pounds heavier at a higher body fat. I have pictures of myself in those exact two scenarios and the same thing holds true. In the leaner photos I look way more jacked even though objectively I was physically a lot smaller.
